<center>
<p><b><font size=+3>7. Impact on the Development Process</font></b></center>

<p><b><font size=+1>Consideration to system specification and construction
changes:</font></b>
<ul>
<li>
The system context(such as requirements, cost, schedule, operating and
support enviromnets)</li>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>
The Capabilites legacy systems and products in the marketplace for components.</li>
</ul>

<p><br><b><font size=+1>Development process changes</font></b>
<ul>
<li>
from a top-down partitioning to a bottom-up assembly of avilable Components</li>
</ul>

<p><br><b><font size=+1>Not only engineering activities such as requirements
specification change to support simultaneous consideration of system requirements
and the marketplace, but so must acquisition processes and contracting
strategies.</font></b>
<p><b><font size=+1>The design, development, and maintenance of component-based
systems, and the migration of legacy systems towards components are complex.</font></b>
